column11:
  Using the expansion in a Fourier-Gegenbauer series, we prove several
identities that extend and generalize known results. In particular, it is
proved among other results, that
  \begin{equation*}
  \sum_{n=0}^\infty\frac{1}{4^n}\binom{2n}{n}\frac{z-2n}{\binom{z-1/2}{n}}\binom{z}{n}^3
  =\frac{\tan(\pi z)}{\pi}
  \end{equation*}
  for all complex numbers $z$ such that $\Re(z)>-\frac{1}{2}$ and
$z\notin\frac{1}{2}+\mathbb{Z}$.
